	<JackHarperStoryteller.Window_IllusiveMan.IllusiveMan>Illusive man</JackHarperStoryteller.Window_IllusiveMan.IllusiveMan>
	<JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.Hatred>Hatred</JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.Hatred>
	<JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.HatredDesc>Hatred: {0}
The Illusive man hatred grows with each human you kill. It doesn't matter if the human killed was your enemy or not. Hatred decreases with time, and also if you release captive humans. Filling the hatred bar will enrage the Illusive Man.</JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.HatredDesc>
	<JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.Honour>Honour</JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.Honour>
	<JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.HonourDesc>Honour: {0}
The Illusive man honour is increased by killing xenos, insects, and hostile mechanoids. Filling the honour bar will result in a reward.</JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.HonourDesc>
	<JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.GainRewardLabel>Illusive man reward</JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.GainRewardLabel>
	<JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.GainRewardText>The Illusive man is pleased with your perseverance in the fight against the enemies of humanity. You can choose a reward or refuse it. Rejecting the reward will reduce the hatred bar.</JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.GainRewardText>
	<JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.Cancel>Refuse</JackHarperStoryteller.GameComponent_IllusiveManStoryteller.Cancel>
